                <exercise>
                    <title>Problems</title>
                    <task workspace="4in">
                        <statement>
                            <p>
                               Let <m>A \subseteq \mathbb{R}</m>.
Prove that <m>A</m> has a maximum if and only if <m>A</m> has a supremum and <m>\mathrm{sup}(A) \in A</m>, in which case <m>\mathrm{max}(A) = \sup(A)</m>.
                            </p>
                        </statement>
                    </task>

                    <task workspace="4in">
                        <statement>
                            <p>
                               Let <m>A \subseteq \mathbb{R}</m> such that <m>A</m> is bounded above and let <m>b</m> be an upper bound of <m>A</m>.
Prove that <m>b</m> is the supremum of <m>A</m> if and only if for every <m>\epsilon \gt 0</m>, there exists <m>a \in A</m> such that <m>b - \epsilon \lt a</m>.
                            </p>
                        </statement>
                    </task>

